      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem">Budget Tool Storage That Holds Up: 8 Contractor-Tested Tool Boxes Under $100</h1>
      <div style="color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem">June 17, 2026 · 8 min read</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every contractor knows the feeling: you've just spent $800 on a new circular saw, $400 on an impact driver set, and $200 on hand tools — and now you need something to store them all. The temptation to grab the cheapest plastic box on the shelf is real, but a box that cracks on the first cold morning or lets moisture ruin your tools is no bargain at any price.</p>
      <p>The good news is that you don't need to spend premium money to get premium tool storage. There are excellent budget-friendly options that deliver genuine durability, smart organization, and years of service. Here are our top picks for contractors who want quality without the premium markup.</p>

      <h2>What Makes a Tool Box "Budget-Friendly" but Still Professional-Grade?</h2>
      <p>Before we dive into specific products, let's define what separates a cheap box that will let you down from an affordable box that will hold up:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Material thickness:</strong> Budget boxes use polypropylene or ABS plastic instead of steel or aluminium. The difference between a good budget box and a bad one is the thickness and density of the plastic. Thinner walls flex and crack. Good budget boxes use reinforced ribbing and thick-wall construction.</li>
        <li><strong>Latch quality:</strong> The latch is the first thing to break on a cheap box. Look for metal-reinforced latch hooks or over-centre locking latches even on budget models.</li>
        <li><strong>Handle attachment:</strong> A handle bolted through the body is far more reliable than one held by plastic clips. Check how the handle is attached before you buy.</li>
        <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Even budget boxes can include basic weather seals. While you won't get the IP-rated protection of premium brands, a simple rubber gasket is better than nothing.</li>
      </ul>

